<caption>If 9 goes in, both –3 and 3 come out.  This <emphasis> violates the rule of consistency:</emphasis> no function can do this</caption>
</table><para id="element-899">This asymmetry has the potential to cause a great deal of confusion, but it is a very important aspect of functions.</para>  

